    "comment": "Rationale: Loss of Teneurin-a reduces the apposition of active zones and neurotransmitter clusters at Drosophila neuromuscular junctions as show in Fig. 2.\nFig.3a,c shows that Teneurin-a loss results in microtubule disorganization at the boutons of Drosophila neuromuscular junctions.\nIn agreement with a presynaptic effect, Fig.1 shows that Teneurin-a is presynaptically localized at Drosophila NMJs.\n\n6/11/2017 Pim\n- Teneurins are transsynaptic adhesion molecules that intracellularly couple to various components of the cytoskeleton.. Experimental description: \"Details of Drosophila stocks can be found in Methods.\"",
